  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Asa's efforts for the abolition of idolatry and the establishment of the kingdom. - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 14:1-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The good and right in God's eyes which Asa did is further defined in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 14:2-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". He abolished all the objects of the idolatrous worship. The \"altars of the strangers\" are altars consecrated to foreign gods; from them the בּמות, high places, are distinguished-these latter being illegal places of sacrifice connected with the worship of Jahve (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 15:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The מצּבוה are the statues or monumental columns consecrated to Baal, and אשׁרים the wooden idols, tree-trunks, or trees, which were consecrated to Astarte (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 14:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 16:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Asa at the same time commanded the people to worship Jahve, the God of the fathers, and to follow the law.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]